criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  First neurological event, affecting the right hemisphere or the left hemisphere
             (stroke);

          -  Structural images of the brain lesion available (magnetic resonance or tomographic
             scans);

          -  Full somato-sensory deficit affecting the left hand;

          -  Good (or corrected) visual acuity;

          -  Good proficiency in French;

          -  Right-handed

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Failure to meet the inclusion criteria ;

          -  Presence of general cognitive deficits and/or suspicious of possible cognitive
             deficits;

          -  Presence of difficulty in task's comprehension;

          -  Impossibility to sustain a research session of at least 45minutes (e.g., attentional
             lability);

          -  Precedent additional neurological disorder and/or current or precedent psychiatric
             disease.
